Executive Summary
This ticket documents the planning and development strategy for a personal investment tracking system designed to calculate Romanian investment taxes and support fiscal reporting.
The objective of the project is to create a long-term Excel-based investment tracking file capable of accurately calculating taxes for multiple income categories while remaining transparent, traceable, and legally compliant.
The development process relies on structured AI assistance combined with manual verification and staged development.
Project Objective
The investment tracker must support:
	• Romanian tax calculation requirements
	• long-term portfolio tracking
	• audit-ready financial documentation
	• manual verification of all calculations
The system must remain modular and expandable.
Development Methodology
Based on previous observations regarding AI hallucination risk, the development process follows a strict staged workflow.
Key principles include:
	• one feature implemented at a time
	• no complex multi-module prompts
	• validation after each module
	• transparent formulas and logic
	• manual verification of all calculations
AI is used primarily as a development assistant rather than an autonomous solution builder.
Parallel Development Strategy
Two separate AI interaction approaches are being tested simultaneously:
Approach 1 – Recovery of the existing investment tracker conversation.
The existing chat will be analyzed to determine whether the current file can still be salvaged and improved.
Approach 2 – Creation of a completely new conversation.
A new chat session will be started with a clean architecture and a revised prompting strategy based on lessons learned from previous attempts.
Both approaches will be evaluated in order to determine the most stable and reliable workflow.
Expected Outcome
The final deliverable will be a fully documented investment tracking system capable of calculating Romanian investment taxes and supporting the preparation of fiscal declarations.
